genresAdvancedInfo.name: cypriot hip hop
genresAdvancedInfo.description: A style of hip hop music that originated in Cyprus and is influenced by Greek and Middle Eastern music. It often features Greek and Turkish lyrics and incorporates traditional Cypriot instruments such as the bouzouki and the tzouras. The music is characterized by its upbeat tempo and catchy melodies.
